==English==

===Etymology===
From the Swedish ''trona'' or from the Spanish ''trona'', both derived from the Arabic {{ARchar|[[اطرون]]}} (''atrūn''), which derives from the Arabic {{ARchar|[[نطرون]]}} (''natrūn''); from the Ancient Greek [[νίτρον]] (''nitron''), from the Ancient Egyptian ''ntry''.

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun|-}}
#{{mineralogy}} a [[saline evaporite]], consisting of mixture of [[sodium carbonate]] and [[sodium bicarbonate]].

